Description: Lower body and foot sherd of East Greek pottery bowl; interior: glazed black with reserved disc at centre; red band lined in white on wall and red ring on disc; exterior reserved with black band at bottom of bowl and on exterior of ring foot; reserved underside; graffito on interior and underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.152)
